<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATWOOD'S HUMOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I hope readers won't be put off by the emphasis on pain and poetry in your 
recent review of Margaret Atwood's "Cat's Eye" (Book Review, Feb. 19). Perhaps 
it takes a woman to see that Atwood's is a very funny novel, as well as a 
painful one. I for one am tired of reading about how grim her work is; if you 
like intellectual black humor, no one catches girls growing up and women 
growing older better than she. But then male wrinkles and dewlaps can still be 
termed "distinguished" in this culture. Female readers know otherwise. 
</P>
<P>
MITZI MYERS 
</P>
<P>
FULLERTON 
</P>
