<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: WAITING FOR TRAVOLTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The Experts" -- John Travolta's first film since the 1985 bomb, "Perfect" -- 
won't be coming soon to a theater near you. After brief playdates in Texas and 
Oklahoma last month, the Paramount pic is headed for video -- due on shelves in 
early June, according to Paramount Home Video. 
</P>
<P>
That news took co-producer Jonathan Krane by surprise. Krane -- also Travolta's 
personal manager -- thought that "The Experts" was merely on hold, until after 
the late summer release of Tri-Star's "Daddy's Home," a romantic comedy with 
Travolta opposite Kirstie Alley. 
</P>
<P>
Krane, who produced the latter pic, told us "it would make good marketing sense 
for Paramount to release 'The Experts' after 'Daddy's Home' generates 
attention. . . " 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
