<HEADLINE>
<P>
OUTTAKES: PROVERBIAL PLUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By From Leonard Klady 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sources tell us that Bruce Willis will play the mercurial waiter-con man when 
playwright Lanford Wilson's volatile play, "Burn This," is transformed into a 
film this summer. A hit locally and on Broadway, Willis' part was originated by 
John Malkovich (who earned rave reviews), with Scott Glenn and Eric Roberts 
earning praise when they replaced Malkovich in the showy role. 
</P>
<P>
Producer Ray Stark and director Herbert Ross -- who collaborated on another 
Broadway-success-turned-movie, "Steel Magnolias," due out in September -- 
reteam on the Tri-Star release. 
</P>
<P>
Wilson will adapt his drama for the screen. From Leonard Klady 
</P>
</TEXT>
