<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE MOVIE CHART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by David Pecchia 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Films now going into production: 
</P>
<P>
Confidence (Confidence PTY Ltd.). Shooting in Australia. Bryan Brown 
co-produces (a first for him) and stars with Karen Allen as a con man who 
waltzes into a small town with dubious intentions. Soon, however, he develops 
an affinity for the community and must question his motivations. Executive 
producers Taylor Hackford and Stuart Benjamin. Producers Brown and Ben Gannon. 
Director Michael Jenkins. Screenwriter Tony Morphett. Distributor New Visions 
Pictures. 
</P>
<P>
Men at Work (Epic). Shooting in L.A. Siblings Emilio Estevez and Charlie Sheen 
star in this comedy adventure as a pair of street smart refuse collectors who 
share a penchant for immersing themselves in bizarre situations. Estevez writes 
and directs. Executive producer Irwin Yablans. Producer Cassian Elwes. 
</P>
<P>
Stella (Goldwyn/Touchstone). Shooting in Toronto. Bette Midler steps into the 
1937 Barbara Stanwyck "Stella Dallas" role as a woman who sacrifices everything 
for her daughter. Producers Samuel Goldwyn Jr. and Bonnie Bruckheimer-Martell. 
Director John Erman. Screenwriter Robert Getchell. Also stars John Goodman, 
Stephen Collins, Trini Alvarado and Marsha Mason. Distributor Buena Vista. 
</P>
<P>
The War of the Roses (Gracie). Shooting in Coupeville and L.A. Michael Douglas, 
Kathleen Turner and Danny DeVito (who directs) star in this dark comedy based 
on Warren Adler's novel. The Roses (M.D. and K.T.) wish to end their marriage, 
but neither wishes to leave the house, which soon becomes the setting for 
physical and emotional turmoil. Executive producers Polly Platt and Doug 
Claybourne. Screenwriters Michael Leeson and Adler. Distributor Fox. Christmas 
release. 
</P>
</TEXT>
