<HEADLINE>
<P>
BROWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I suspect that Brown has spent the past years doing fundamental social research 
and, like many of us who have taken a good, long look at where the United 
States is going, has found that the 1990s will see a strong return to values, 
ethics, the family and productivity. And so, Brown is back with a new image of 
values, ethics, the family and productivity. 
</P>
<P>
It is all an act, and if we are not willing to see through it, we'll have to 
put up with his same old weaknesses and phony social programs. 
</P>
<P>
JOE M. TURNER 
</P>
<P>
Vista 
</P>
