<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOOK FOR THE SPRING ISSUE OF TRAVELING IN STYLE TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETTY HUGHES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Don't miss the spring issue of the Traveling in Style magazine in this week's 
Los Angeles Times. Keeping readers on the edge of their seats, journalist Jimmy 
Breslin recalls a spur-of-the-moment trip to Central America with an expired 
passport. Best-selling mystery author Mary Higgins Clark shares the joys of her 
hideaway in Cape Cod. Times Travel Editor Jerry Hulse, with intimate, on-site 
reporting, introduces us to Britain's most celebrated stately home now operated 
by the National Trust as a magnificent hotel for connoisseurs looking for the 
finest in accommodations and service. 
</P>
<P>
Other contributors are astrologer Sydney Omarr, who predicts what the stars say 
about your traveling plans this year. Dr. Harvey Ruben gives pros and cons 
about couples taking separate vacations, and Jennifer Merin takes us on a 
shopping spree to some of the most splendid emporiums in the world. Through the 
camera's eye of Times photographer Iris Schneider, travel aboard the 
Trans-Siberian Express on a three-day journey across the Soviet Union. And 
there's much more. 
</P>
<P>
Look for the Traveling in Style magazine in this Sunday's Los Angeles Times. 
BETTY HUGHES 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031989-0069 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 32701 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
