<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA031989-0084 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 32734 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 19, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
San Gabriel Valley; Part 9; Page 6; Column 2 
</P>
</SECTION>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, A Bright Spot in Arcadia: A peacock greets visitors to the State and 
County Arboretum, where dazzling flowers attract honey bees and a sundial is 
compared to a timepiece worn on the wrist. The arboretum, 301 N. Baldwin Ave., 
Arcadia, is open every day from 9 a.m. to 4:30 p.m., and general admission is 
$3. LOU MACK / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
