</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fresno United Way Executive Director Tony Folcarelli will take over the top 
staff job of the statewide volunteer organization, it has been disclosed. As 
United Way of California executive director, the 54-year-old Folcarelli will 
assist the state's 41 United Ways in management, training and other phases of 
charity fund-raising. Folcarelli, who was associate regional manager of United 
Way in the West Los Angeles area from 1971 to 1974, was credited with 
revitalizing the Fresno operation by insisting that traditional agencies 
document the effectiveness of their programs. This opened the door to some 
community groups previously denied allocations. Folcarelli will assume the post 
May 1. 
</P>
