About a foot of snow fell over portions of Michigan and thunderstorms lingered 
in the South after dropping hail the size of baseballs in Oklahoma, the 
National Weather Service said. Winter storm warnings were posted over northern 
and central Maine, northern New Hampshire, northern Vermont and northeast New 
York state. The snowfall in Michigan included 12 inches at Cadillac and 11 
inches at Kalkaska and Hart. 
