<HEADLINE>
<P>
RESTAURANT OWNER IS STUFFED IN CAR TRUNK DURING ROBBERY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The owner of a smorgasbord restaurant was robbed at gunpoint and kidnapped in 
his own vehicle by two men Friday, police reported. 
</P>
<P>
Helge Hensen, proprietor of the Nordic Inn, 3577 Midway Drive, was leaving 
around 9:20 p.m. when he was approached by two men. The men first robbed him of 
the cash receipts at gunpoint and then forced Hensen into the passenger 
compartment of his car. 
</P>
<P>
A cap was placed over Hensen's head, and he was later forced into the car's 
trunk. 
</P>
<P>
The men drove around for several hours. California Highway Patrol officers 
attempted to pull the car over for what they suspected to be drunken driving 
but were fired at by the suspects. No one was hit, but a round struck the 
cruiser's radiator, preventing the officers from pursuing the suspects. 
</P>
<P>
The suspects drove to 3000 Rue D'Orleans, where they abandoned the car with 
Hensen still in the trunk. When Hensen realized the suspects had left, he 
banged on the trunk door for about 25 minutes. A passer-by released him. 
</P>
<P>
The first suspect was described as a white male in his late 30s, with short, 
graying black hair and several days' beard growth. The second suspect was 
described as a male, possibly black, in his late 20s, with short, dark curly 
hair. 
</P>
