<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVER KILLED IN FREEWAY ACCIDENT; 3 UNHURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A motorist was killed Saturday afternoon when the car he was driving in excess 
of 100 m.p.h. on the Simi Valley Freeway crashed, a California Highway Patrol 
spokeswoman said. Three passengers, however, escaped injury. 
</P>
<P>
The driver, who officials said had been drinking, apparently lost control of 
the vehicle when he reached down to adjust his radio about 1:30 p.m., the 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
The car, which was approaching College View Avenue in Moorpark, skidded across 
both westbound lanes, struck an embankment on the shoulder and rolled several 
times. 
</P>
<P>
The driver, who was not wearing a seat belt, was killed. His identity was not 
released. 
</P>
<P>
The passengers, who also were drinking, were not hurt, the CHP said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
