<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEPULVEDA JUNIOR HIGH TEAM WINS L.A. SCHOOLS' ACADEMIC PENTATHLON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For the second time in three years, a team from Sepulveda Junior High School 
has won the Los Angeles Unified School District's Academic Pentathlon 
competition. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm excited for the school and for the kids who have worked so hard," said 
Melodye Wiens, coach of the nine-member Sepulveda team. 
</P>
<P>
The Sepulveda team finished second last year but won in 1987, Wiens said. The 
sixth annual competition was held Feb. 25, but the results were announced on 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Four other San Fernando Valley junior highs also scored high among the 80 
schools that competed in essay writing, social studies, math, science and a 
category called "Super Quiz." 
</P>
<P>
Reed Junior High School of North Hollywood finished second; Porter Junior High 
School of Granada Hills was fourth, and Hale Junior High School of Woodland 
Hills was fifth. 
</P>
<P>
The third-place team was from the Los Angeles Center for Enriched Studies. 
</P>
<P>
More than 700 students participated in the competition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
