<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEAN ELLIOTT SCORES 25 AS ARIZONA BREEZES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BOISE, Ida. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sean Elliott scored 25 points, and top-ranked Arizona held Clemson scoreless 
for more than nine minutes Saturday to beat the Tigers, 94-68, and advance to 
the semifinals of the National Collegiate Athletic Assn. West Regional. 
</P>
<P>
The Wildcats (29-3) led by 14 in the first half and withstood a Clemson rally 
in the opening minutes of the second before pulling away to their 11th straight 
victory and fourth straight blowout. 
</P>
<P>
Arizona plays No. 15 Nevada-Las Vegas Thursday night in Denver. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Muehlebach scored 19 for Arizona, including four three-pointers. His two 
three-point baskets helped lift the Wildcats out of trouble after Clemson cut 
the lead to four early in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
Clemson (19-11) went 9 minutes 22 seconds without scoring in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
The Tigers led, 25-23, on Ricky Jones' 19-foot jumper with 10:11 to play in the 
first half. Arizona, despite a sputtering offense of its own, scored the next 
16 points to take a 39-25 lead on Muehlebach's steal and layup with 4:39 to 
play. 
</P>
<P>
The Tigers finally scored when Derrick Forrest sank a pair of free throws with 
1:49 left in the half. Clemson committed 13 turnovers during the 16-0 Arizona 
streak. 
</P>
<P>
After trailing by nine at halftime, the Tigers came out strong. 
</P>
<P>
A pair of three-pointers by Forrest and a dunk by Eldon Campbell pulled Clemson 
within 49-45 with 16:06 to play. But Muuehlebach hit two three-pointers and 
Elliott scored on a drive to boost the lead back to 57-45 and the Tigers never 
came closer than 10 again. 
</P>
<P>
The Wildcats' biggest lead was the final margin. 
</P>
<P>
Campbell scored 24 and Forrest 21 for the Tigers, the sixth-place finisher in 
the Atlantic Coast Conference. 
</P>
<P>
Jud Buechler added 15 points and Anthony Cook 14 for Arizona. 
</P>
</TEXT>
