<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NAMES IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pete Weber became the third man to win bowling's triple crown when he beat Dave 
Ferraro, 221-216, for the title in the $280,000 Professional Bowlers Assn. 
National Championship at Toledo, Ohio. Weber, who also won the 1987 Tournament 
of Champions and the 1988 U.S. Open, joined Billy Hardwick and Johnny Petraglia 
as triple crown winners. 
</P>
</TEXT>
