<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ram wide receiver Michael Young, an unprotected free agent, said he has agreed 
in terms to a contract with the Denver Broncos. 
</P>
<P>
Young, 26, who earned $162,000 last season, is expected to sign a two-year deal 
(one year with an option) with the Broncos Monday worth almost $500,000, 
including signing bonus and incentives. 
</P>
<P>
"Can you believe that," Young said, "For me?" 
</P>
<P>
Young, a sixth-round pick of the Rams in 1985, has played sparingly in his 
four-year career. He had only two receptions for 27 yards last season and 
finished it on injured reserve with a back injury. 
</P>
