<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: REPORT: FOR SUTTON, IT'S QUIT OR BE FIRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If Eddie Sutton doesn't resign, he is expected to be fired within a few days as 
basketball coach at the University of Kentucky, the Louisville Courier-Journal 
reported Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said action could be taken this week at the board of directors 
meeting of the Kentucky Athletic Assn. 
</P>
<P>
In an interview with CBS-TV, Sutton, who is 90-40 at Kentucky, said "that (his 
future) may come up, but I have not been asked to resign at this point." 
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted anonymous sources as saying that although Sutton is not 
named in the 18 National Collegiate Athletic Assn. allegations, the school 
wants him out. 
</P>
<P>
If Sutton's contract is terminated, Kentucky would still be obligated to pay 
off the remaining year at $80,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
