<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Darryl Strawberry, New York Mets outfielder, was involved in two shoving 
incidents during the sixth inning of an exhibition game against the Toronto 
Blue Jays at Dunedin, Fla. 
</P>
<P>
The first altercation started when pitcher Jeff Musselman hit Strawberry in the 
back with a pitch, and the right fielder ran out to the mound. Strawberry was 
tackled by catcher Pat Borders and third baseman Kelly Gruber before he could 
reach Musselman. 
</P>
<P>
Then, when Strawberry advanced to third base, he and Gruber argued briefly and 
began to scuffle. Both benches emptied, the players were separated and 
Strawberry was ejected. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
