<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFING: EVENTS IN THE NEWS THIS WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Huntington Beach City Council will hold a public hearing Tuesday on whether 
to change zoning from commercial to conservation on degraded wetlands 
stretching along Pacific Coast Highway between Beach Boulevard and the Santa 
Ana River. The area has been designated for conservation in the city's general 
plan, but specific zoning of the property stalled in the Planning Commission 
after threats of legal action by two private landowners. 
</P>
<P>
One parcel between Brookhurst Street and the Santa Ana River, known as the 
Talbert Marsh, is already undergoing restoration under the auspices of the 
private Huntington Beach Wetlands Conservancy. Last month, tidal flow was 
restored to the 24-acre parcel. 
</P>
