<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFING: EVENTS IN THE NEWS THIS WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Board of Supervisors will hold a public hearing Wednesday to consider 
raising the annual fees for about 11,000 Orange County businesses that generate 
or store hazardous wastes underground. 
</P>
<P>
The county conducts routine annual inspections of businesses that handle or 
store hazardous wastes. To pay for that inspection, those businesses must pay 
an annual fee, ranging from $165 for a company with fewer than 10 employees to 
$1,002 for companies with more than 500 workers. County health officials have 
proposed a 3.5% to 4% fee increase for all companies. 
</P>
