<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFING: EVENTS IN THE NEWS THIS WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dedication of a $3.3-million hangar project named in memory of veteran pilot 
and radio traffic reporter Bruce Wayne will be held Tuesday at Fullerton 
Municipal Airport. A bronze plaque cast with Wayne's image will be unveiled at 
the ceremony. The City Council voted to name the new 56-unit hanger as a 
memorial to the Fullerton resident, who was killed in June, 1986, when his 
single-engine Cessna crashed shortly after takeoff from the airport. 
