<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANIMAL DEATHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding the article concerning the multiple killings of Tustin resident pets 
(Orange County section, March 10): 
</P>
<P>
Excuse me, please? Did I read correctly that Tustin area pets found dead with 
almost no blood in their bodies, severed paws and "washed organs" are being 
explained away as coyote kills? 
</P>
<P>
Are coyotes getting tidy these days? Well, I just think it's so kind of the 
coyotes to leave the kitties nicely arranged for the owners to find later. 
</P>
<P>
Golly, when I lived in coyote country, four of my kitties and many of my 
neighbors' pets disappeared without a trace, and the coyotes never left so much 
as a brief note. 
</P>
<P>
The other theory, that the animals were killed while trying to keep warm in car 
engines, was, to say the least, creative. 
</P>
<P>
J. LUND 
</P>
<P>
Huntington Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
