COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
PETERS' HITTING STREAK HITS 22 GAMES; TITANS WIN 16TH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rex Peters of Cal State Fullerton had a single in the second inning to extend 
his hitting streak to 22 games as the Titans defeated Gonzaga, 12-4, in a 
nonconference baseball game Saturday at Titan Field. 
</P>
<P>
Peters, a senior, was two for three and has hit safely in all of Fullerton's 
games. Brent Mayne hit in a school-record 38 consecutive games last season. 
Fullerton (16-6) scored nine runs on 10 hits in the second inning. Mayne and 
Dave Staton had two hits each in the inning. Staton also had two RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
Danny DeVille (3-0) pitched the first five innings for the victory. Gonzaga is 
5-2. 
</P>
<P>
In a Golden State Athletic Conference baseball doubleheader: 
</P>
<P>
