<P>
KEY TO RESIDENTIAL BUILDERS ROSTER -- The name of each company is followed by 
its headquarters city and then by its principal officer. Sales figures are 
given for 1988 and have been confined to residential sales in Kern, Los 
Angeles, Orange, Riverside, San Bernardino, San Diego and Ventura counties. 
Sales projections are for anticipated residential sales in the above-mentioned 
counties for 1989. The number of units constructed in 1988 includes units 
completed for sale during 1988 and is broken out by number and percent of each 
type of unit: single-family homes, apartments and condominiums (including units 
in planned unit developments). Inventory includes any units completed for sale 
that were unsold by the end of the accounting period. NOTES FOR THE 18th ANNUAL 
SURVEY RESIDENTIAL BUILDING Note: Ranking based on rounded sales figures. 
Subtotals may not add to 100% due to computer rounding. Firms with the same 
1988 sales volume are ranked in alphabetical order. * Firm reporting on 
fiscal-year basis. ** Includes an 80-unit dormitory at Whittier College. + The 
following builders changed their name in 1988: Broadmoor Homes from Broadmoor 
Homes Southwest Inc.; Calstar Equities Inc. from Calstar Construction Inc.; 
Campbell Contractors from Campbell General Contractors; Covington Development 
Group Inc. From Covington Technologies; D&amp;S Development Corp. from D&amp;S 
Co.; J.C.C. Development from J.C.C. Enterprises Inc.; Sumitomo Realty &amp; 
Development Ca. Inc. from La Solana Corp.; Weston Development Corp. from Weston 
Communities. ALPHABETICAL LISTINGS Following is an alphabetical listing of the 
building leaders included in The Times' 18th annual survey, with the rank of 
each firm. Asterisk indicates a tie in the ranking. 
