<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS BRIEFS: BUILDER OFFERS TO BUY BACK HOMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID M. KINCHEN From staff reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The chairman of the board of Shapell Industries Inc., Nathan Shapell, has 
offered to buy the houses of dissatisfied owners in the Kite Hill tract in 
Laguna Niguel. 
</P>
<P>
At least half a dozen homeowners have sued S &amp; S Construction Co., the 
home-building unit of Shapell Industries, since 1984, alleging that the builder 
and subcontractors failed to correctly grade the site and test and compact the 
soil. Still another lawsuit contends that there is poor plumbing, design and 
construction in a house in the tract. 
</P>
<P>
Shapell said he would pay the original owners who have lived in their houses 
since the tract open a decade ago double their purchase prices in cash. He will 
not require proof that any work done by S &amp; S Construction Co. caused the 
defects. 
</P>
<P>
"We do not want anybody to live in an S &amp; S home who isn't happy," Shapell 
said. The company has built an estimated 60,000 houses in California since it 
was organized 34 years ago including 40,000 in Orange County, according to S 
&amp; S spokesman Richard Mahan, who added that so far, no one has taken 
Shapell up on his buy-back offer. DAVID M. KINCHENFrom staff reports 
</P>
