<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS BRIEFS: RECLAIMED-WATER LINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID M. KINCHEN From staff reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Glendale will build a $1.5-million pipeline to move water from the Los 
Angeles-Glendale water reclamation plant on the east bank of the Los Angeles 
River to Forest Lawn cemetery two miles away. 
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement approved by the Glendale City Council, Forest Lawn will 
receive up to 200 million gallons of reclaimed water each year to landscaped 
the cemetery's 125 acres of lawns. Forest Lawn will pay for the treated sewage 
water at a rate of 75% of the cost of drinking water. DAVID M. KINCHENFrom 
staff reports 
</P>
