<P>
JAPANESE PURCHASE BEACH CITY BUILDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Japanese firm, Balzak Corp. of Osaka, has purchased a three-story, 
63,888-square-foot building at 225 S. Sepulveda Blvd., Manhattan Beach, for $16 
million from Treehouse Associates of Morristown, N.J. 
</P>
<P>
The 3-year-old building was developed by Loomis &amp; Eick. Balzak was 
represented by the Seeley Co., and Treehouse was represented by Coldwell Banker 
Commercial Real Estate Services. 
</P>
