<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMERCIAL SCENE; 
</P>
<P>
SHOPPING CENTER SET ON 22.5 ACRES IN SANTEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
First City-Santee Town Center, a joint venture, has purchased 22.5 acres at the 
corner of Mission Gorge and Town Center Drive in Santee from The Hahn Co. 
</P>
<P>
The developers, First City-California II and Santee Town Center Associates, a 
limited partnership with La Jolla Pacific Development Group, are planning to 
build a $23-million, 235,000-square-foot shopping center on the site. 
</P>
<P>
Construction of Santee Town Center, which will emulate the old- fashioned town 
squares of the 1800's settlements, will begin in May with an estimated project 
completion in early 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
