<P>
UC SAN DIEGO SIGNS LEASE ON WAREHOUSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UC San Diego has signed a $3.6-million, 10-year lease for 55,000 square feet of 
space in the Miramar Distribution Center, a 293,000-square-foot warehouse 
complex at 7835 Trade St., San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
The space will be used to house the university's in-house graphics department 
and for storage purposes. The San Diego office of John Burnham &amp; Co. 
Commercial Real Estate represented the university in the negotiations and the 
San Diego office of Coldwell Banker Commercial Real Estate represented the 
owner, Sudberry Properties Inc. 
</P>
